      <div type="book">
        <linkGrp type="notes"/>
        <div n="972-S899" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1">By Doctor R──────fe,</l></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-1">Sir,</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="2" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-2"><hi rend="display-initial">I</hi>N reading your Letter alone in my Hackney,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-3"> Your Damnable Riddle my poor Brains did rack nigh,</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-4"> And when with much Labour the matter I crackt,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-5"> I found you mistaken in Matter of Fact.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-6"> A Woman's no <hi rend="underline">Sieve</hi> for with that you begin,</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-7"> Because she let's out, more than she takes in.</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-8"> And that a Woman's a <hi rend="underline">Riddle</hi> can never be right,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-9"> For a <hi rend="underline">Riddle</hi> is dark, but a Woman is light.</l><l n="10" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-10"> But hold────you shall see, I can say something archer,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-11"> Pray what is a Man? he's a fine Linnen Searcher.</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-12"> Now tell me a Thing that wants Interpretation,</l><l n="13" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-13"> What Name for a Maid, was the first Man's Damnation.</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-14"> If your Worship will please t'explain me this <hi rend="underline">Rebus</hi>,</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-972-S899-line-15"> I swear from hence forwards you shall be my <hi rend="underline">Ph<unclear>oe</unclear>bus</hi>.<gap/></l></lg></div>
